title: Doctor Who DWO Whocast 71 Podcast (24 May 2008) - Moffett
description:
Doctor Who DWO Whocast 71 Podcast (24 May 2008) - Moffett


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

In this week&#039;s episode of the DWO WhoCast... The 2T&#039;s bring you an exclusive interview with the Doctor&#039;s Daughter herself, Georgia Moffett, as she discusses her time on Doctor Who, how much of a fan her son is of the show, and her recent work on the Spooks Code 9 TV series. 

The boys also review the most recent episode, 4.7: The Unicorn and the Wasp, and there are a few competitions on the go too. The fandom corner fan trap competition is still running where you get to decide the name of the segment, as well as a new competition centered around the Ribos Operation.

Opening story is on the announcement that Peter Moffett (no relation to Peter Davison&#039;s Daughter Georgia Moffett) taking over for RTD and how the show can be better without Russell T. Davies and the mal-aligned gay agenda that people are tired of, etc.  

Also includes a review of The Unicorn and the Wasp.  


Excellent episode!
